{"cursor":"1684","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox comic book title  |title = The\nSchoolgirl |image= |caption = Click on to enlarge |schedule = Weekly |format =\n|ongoing=n |publisher = Amalgamated Press |date = 21 February 1922 â 13 March\n1923 3 August 1929 â 18 May 1940 |issues = |main_char_team =\n|writers = |artists = |pencillers = |inkers = |colorists = |editors=\n|creative_team_month = |creative_team_year = |creators = |subcat=Amalgamated\nPress Comics |sort= }} 'The Schoolgirl' was a British 28-page weekly story paper\naimed at girls, subsequently reduced to 24 pages. Launched on 21 February\n1922, it was published by . The first series ended on 13 March 1923, but the\ntitle was revived on 3 August 1929 and continued until 18 May 1940, when paper\nrationing during the Second World War resulted in its merger with [[Girls\nCrystal]].\n\nMost stories centred around the girls and staff of Cliff House School, a\nfictional establishment in Kent, on a cliff top overlooking the sea. Cliff House\nwas the sister school of Greyfriars, where Billy Bunter was educated, and had\nits own equivalent, his sister Bessie Bunter.\n","linknr":99,"url":"The_Schoolgirl","recorded":1375060783,"links":["/w/index.php?title=The_Schoolgirl&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=The_Schoolgirl&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&